                <note rend="inline" type="source">368.117/44: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-18T18:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1919—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 19—1:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>861. An official from the Greek Ministry of Foreign Affairs has notified me
                    formally that American citizens of Greek origin and all other Greeks who have
                    served in the American Army, will be exempted from further service in the Greek
                    Army.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
